```rust
pub fn sef_startup(cfg: SefConfig) -> Result<Sef, i32> {
    // SYS_GETINFO(GET_WHOAMI) to kernel (SENDREC to SYSTEM)
    let mut msg = Message { m_source: 0, m_type: SYS_GETINFO, payload: [0u8; 96] };
    msg.payload[0..4].copy_from_slice(&GET_WHOAMI.to_ne_bytes());

    let trap_rc = ipc_sendrec(boot_endpoint(SYSTEM), &mut msg);
    if trap_rc != OK || msg.m_type != OK { return Err(...); }

    let endpoint = i32::from_ne_bytes(msg.payload[0..4].try_into()?);
    let mut name = [0u8; SYS_GETINFO_NAME_LEN];
    name.copy_from_slice(&msg.payload[12..12 + SYS_GETINFO_NAME_LEN]);

    let sef = Sef { endpoint, name, signal_handler: cfg.signal_handler };

    if let Some(init) = cfg.init_fresh {
        let rc = init(endpoint, &name);
        if rc != OK { return Err(rc); }
    }
    Ok(sef)
}
```

**Sef::receive** (lines 99–138):
```rust
pub fn receive(&self, msg: &mut Message) -> i32 {
    loop {
        let rc = ipc_receive(ANY, msg);
        if rc != OK { return rc; }
        match classify(msg) {
            SefEvent::Application => return OK,
            SefEvent::Ping => {
                // Heartbeat from RS; ack via notify (errors ignored)
                let _ = ipc_notify(boot_endpoint(RS_PROC_NR));
            }
            SefEvent::Signal(signo) => {
                if let Some(handler) = self.signal_handler {
                    handler(signo);
                }
            }
            SefEvent::Init => { /* re-init request from RS — deferred */ }
        }
    }
}
```

**classify.rs** → `/Users/kevinbarnard/src/minixrs/server-rt/src/classify.rs` (lines 50–66)

**SEF control message discrimination** (lines 50–66):
```rust
pub fn classify(msg: &Message) -> SefEvent {
    let rs = boot_endpoint(RS_PROC_NR);
    let pm = boot_endpoint(PM_PROC_NR);
    match msg.m_type {
        NOTIFY_MESSAGE if msg.m_source == rs => SefEvent::Ping,
        SEF_SIGNAL if msg.m_source == pm || msg.m_source == rs => {
            let signo = i32::from_ne_bytes(msg.payload[0..4].try_into()?);
            SefEvent::Signal(signo)
        }
        SEF_INIT if msg.m_source == rs => SefEvent::Init,
        _ => SefEvent::Application,
    }
}
```

**Ping mechanism** → `/Users/kevinbarnard/src/minixrs/kernel-shared/src/callnr.rs`
- **No `SEF_PING` constant** — ping is delivered as `NOTIFY_MESSAGE` with `m_source == RS`
- RS sends: `ipc_notify(server_endpoint)`
- Server receives: `m_type == NOTIFY_MESSAGE && m_source == RS_PROC_NR`
- Server acks: `ipc_notify(boot_endpoint(RS_PROC_NR))`

**SEF control message range**:
- `SEF_RQ_BASE = 0xD00`
- `SEF_INIT = SEF_RQ_BASE (0xD00)`
- `SEF_SIGNAL = SEF_RQ_BASE + 1 (0xD01)`
- Ping: `NOTIFY_MESSAGE` (0x1000) with source check, not a numbered request

