**init_boot_image function** (lines 352–423):
```rust
fn populate_priv(id: PrivId, entry: &BootEntry, n_active: u16) {
    let pr = unsafe { priv_slot_mut(id) }?;
    pr.flags = entry.priv_flags;
    pr.trap_mask = entry.trap_mask;

    if entry.trap_mask == SRV_T {
        // SRV_T privs can send to every active slot [0, n_active)
        fill_bits(&mut pr.ipc_to, n_active as usize);
        // SRV_T privs can issue every kernel call defined in Phase 4
        fill_bits(&mut pr.k_call_mask, NR_KERN_CALLS_PHASE4);
    }
    pr.sig_mgr = boot_endpoint(RS_PROC_NR);  // RS is signal manager
}
```

**For RS, init_boot_image automatically provides**:
- **ipc_to**: bits [0, n_active) — can IPC to every active boot server (DS, VM, SCHED, VFS, PM)
- **k_call_mask**: all bits set via `fill_bits(&mut pr.k_call_mask, NR_KERN_CALLS_PHASE4)` — can issue `SYS_SETALARM`, `SYS_GETINFO`, etc.
- **sig_mgr**: already set to `boot_endpoint(RS_PROC_NR)` for all servers (RS manages signals)

